NHL ENTRY DRAFT
June 27, 1998
Vitaly Vishnevsky
START_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT
 
 
  
 
  
  
   
 
VITALI VISHNEVSKY:   I am most happy to be drafted by Anaheim.  They are very nice people.  It is very strong physically.  He's a tough player.  He is a good skater.  For offensive game also it is very successful. 
 

Q.  (Question in Russian)?
 
VITALI VISHNEVSKY:   And powerplay specifically. 
 

Q.  (In Russian)?
 
VITALI VISHNEVSKY:   Actually everything needs some improvement but slapshot specifically. 
 

Q.  (Question in Russian)?
 
VITALI VISHNEVSKY:   The atmosphere is good. 
 

Q.  (Question in Russian)?
 
VITALI VISHNEVSKY:   He follows up NHL development. Unfortunately, there is not much chance to watch all NHL games in Russia, but every time he gets a chance, he watches those games which are broadcast on local TV.  Of course, from now on, he will be paying more attention to this specific team. 
 

Q.  (Question in Russian)?
 
VITALI VISHNEVSKY:   All we know, he is going to play there.  That's all he knows now. 
 

End of FastScripts... 

END_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT